name: Minnesota State Capitol
description: The Minnesota State Capitol is the seat of government for the U.S. state of Minnesota, located in its capital city of Saint Paul. Designed by architect Cass Gilbert and completed in 1905, it is one of the finest examples of Beaux-Arts architecture in America.

address.street: 75 Rev Dr Martin Luther King Jr Blvd

historicalEvents.title: Capitol Building Completed
historicalEvents.description: The Minnesota State Capitol building was officially completed after four years of construction.

name: Cathedral of Saint Paul
description: The Cathedral of Saint Paul is a Roman Catholic cathedral and the co-cathedral of the Archdiocese of Saint Paul and Minneapolis. Designed by Emmanuel Louis Masqueray in the Beaux-Arts style, it was completed in 1915.

name: Science Museum of Minnesota
description: The Science Museum of Minnesota is a science museum in downtown Saint Paul. Founded in 1907, it is one of the premier science museums in the United States.

name: Fort Snelling
description: Fort Snelling is a former military fortification and National Historic Landmark located at the confluence of the Minnesota and Mississippi Rivers. Built between 1819 and 1825, it played a significant role in the westward expansion of the United States.
